          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "BRST",
                  "POLPS",
                  "TAGD"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The electron beam with energy",
                "192.7MeV was extracted from the MAX-I storage ring,",
                "which worked in a stretcher mode. Then the beam was",
                "delivered into experimental area and was directed onto",
                "photon radiators. The beam size on the radiators was",
                "no more than 2 mm, and the electron current was about",
                "5...10 nA. The polarized photon beam has been",
                "produced at process of a coherent bremsstrahlung of",
                "electrons in a diamond crystal of 100 mu-m thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two targets, a 1.1mm CH2 and a 1mm CD2 thickness",
                "plates, were used for measurements. The targets were",
                "positioned on the distance about 2 m from the photon",
                "collimator at angle 30 degrees to the photon beam",
                "direction. The numbers of carbon nuclei per cm2 were",
                "0.885e22 cm-2 for the CH2 target and 0.771e22 cm-2",
                "for the CD2 target, the number of deuteron nuclei per",
                "cm2 was 1.541e22 cm-2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "CSICR",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons were detected by a CsI/SSD",
                "telescope, placed under angle 90 degrees to the beam",
                "axis. It consisted of two identical single-sided",
                "silicon strip detectors and a CsI(Tl) counter, which",
                "functioned as deltaE and E detectors, respectively.",
                "The SSDs had a thickness of 0.5 mm and 64 strips,",
                "each of 1 mm width, which were paralleled in groups",
                "of two for the read-out, thus yielding an effective",
                "strip width of 2 mm. The CsI(Tl) detector was of",
                "cylinder shape of 12.5 cm in diameter and 10 cm long,",
                "housed in Al container."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented.",
                " The systematic uncertainty was estimated to be about",
                " 10%, and arises from error of the random background",
                " spectra normalization at the background subtraction",
                " (about 7%), and accuracy of the polarization",
                " determination (about 5%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
